# If you fork this repo to run your own real model, cognitive-model/hypotheses,
# sessions, and experiments will fill up with real personal data. Uncomment the
# lines below to keep that data out of git entirely (and consider making your
# fork private too):
# cognitive-model/hypotheses/*
# !cognitive-model/hypotheses/H000-example-notification-checking.md
# cognitive-model/sessions/*
# !cognitive-model/sessions/README.md
# cognitive-model/experiments/*
# !cognitive-model/experiments/README.md
